    "body": "These are the relevant docs I believe:\nhttps://github.com/atom/atom-shell/blob/master/docs/api/menu.md\n\nIn a nutshell you create a new Menu() from require(\"menu\") and append as many new MenuItems() from require(\"menu-item\") to it as you want.\n\nWhen you're done you set Menu.setApplicationMenu(menu) where Menu is the handle for require(\"menu\") and menu is your composed new Menu() object.\n\nSo in essence you don't remove them, you overwrite the entire menu with a new one that doesn't have them.\n"
